comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T21:59:23.505Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: prior all-status audits are completed point-in-time reviews and pm-e9zh owns terminal resolution evidence; none owns a future resumable typed-relationship reconstruction program. This plan starts only after pm-6x7o."
body: "## Wave strategy\n\n0. Freeze and publish a reproducible baseline; classify current roots, active dependency isolates, aliases, and body-to-edge mismatches.\n1. Enrich active strategic stories, features, decisions, and delivery chains with high-confidence explicit evidence.\n2. Normalize legacy edge aliases and repair semantic integrity after ADR acceptance.\n3. Backfill recent terminal lineages in changelog-safe batches, then move backward by history epoch.\n4. Reconstruct evidence, incident, release, package, and domain relationships from immutable events and linked resources.\n5. Verify million-item and federated behavior, sample quality manually, and retain a waiver and uncertainty ledger.\n\n## Safety\n\nNo generic-density target. No all-items full dump. No terminal touch outside a dedicated batch. No automatic edge whose source and confidence cannot be explained. A correction appends a superseding event rather than erasing proof."
